      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "TRICKY MICKY (1) was out of the placings last time but shapes well for this on his sharp win a few runs back, getting around this track over 411m in 23.31. Can return to winning form here if runs up to best figures. DRILL BABY (3) has some solid form under her belt and proved too classy last time to win by 0.8 lengths at this track in a handy 23.80 beating Charli's Begonia. Ran one of the fastest times on the program in her latest win. Makes plenty of appeal on the back of that last-start win. KOORINGA KATE (7) jumped well to win over the 300m at this track two runs back then raced on speed again when finishing second at this track last start. Expected to be in this for a long way. COUNTRY FORM (2) has a solid strike rate at this track and distance.",
